OL,3,CZero hours contracts restriction among
OL,4,Cproposals to strengthen workers' rights
OL,6,FAt present, employees need to be in a
OL,7,Fjob for six months before employers
OL,8,Fare obliged to consider such a request.
OL,10,FThe plan also seeks to address issues
OL,11,Faround the "misclassification" of
OL,12,Fpeople as being self-employed, when
OL,13,Fthey are effectively employed workers.
OL,15,FThose categorised as self-employed are
OL,16,Fnot entitled to rights afforded to
OL,17,Fstaff, such as paid leave and receipt
OL,18,Fof the national minimum wage.
OL,20,FSuch laws would be relevant to some
OL,21,Fdelivery drivers and similar jobs.
